This paper proposes a novel generative adversarial network (GAN) for zero-shot learning, which involves synthesizing CNN features conditioned on class-level semantic information. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of semantic information and classification loss suggests that the paper may also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the use of multimodal embedding methods suggests that the paper may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
